<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>FRONT DRIVE AXLE WHEEL ENDS: ROCKWELL - ASSEMBLY - POWER STEERING ADJUSTMENT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>POWER STEERING ADJUSTMENT</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>The power units must be stopped before the axle stop touches the housing to prevent unnecessary
                    stressing to the axle components.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mechanical Relief (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200837">Figure 37</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200837" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg02/G0200837.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 37. Steering Stop Adjustment (Power Steering - Mechanical Relief)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. 1/8" CLEARANCE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FULL TURN POSITION</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. STOPSCREW AND JAM NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. MAXIMUM TURNING ANGLE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Vehicles with mechanical Pitman arm stops or cylinder stops must be adjusted to end the travel of the
                Pitman arm or cylinder 1/8" before the steering stop screw touches the housing. Maximum turn angle is
                then controlled by the arm or cylinder stop, not the axle stop. Make the adjustments for both full right
                and full left turns.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Hydraulic Relief (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200838">Figure 38</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200838" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg02/G0200838.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 38. Steering Stop Adjustment (Power Steering - Hydraulic Relief)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. 3/16" - 1/4" SPACER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FULL TURN POSITION</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. STOPSCREW AND JAM NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. MAXIMUM TURNING ANGLE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Hydraulic steering gears or cylinders with poppet valves must be adjusted while a 1/4" to 3/16" spacer
                is held between the housing and stop screw. The poppet valves must be adjusted to permit pressure bypass
                at this position with the spacer in place for full right and full left turns. During this setting, the
                steering gear pressure must be at a maximum, 600 psi.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
